{"type":"user.message","data":{"content":"I'm writing MSTest tests for a factory method. Is there a better MSTest assertion to check the returned type instead of hard casting?\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()\n{\n    var factory = new HandlerFactory();\n    var result = factory.Create(\"email\");\n\n    var handler = (EmailHandler)result;\n    Assert.IsNotNull(handler);\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", handler.Type);\n}\n```\n","transformedContent":"<current_datetime>2026-05-13T15:10:40.121Z</current_datetime>\n\nI'm writing MSTest tests for a factory method. Is there a better MSTest assertion to check the returned type instead of hard casting?\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()\n{\n    var factory = new HandlerFactory();\n    var result = factory.Create(\"email\");\n\n    var handler = (EmailHandler)result;\n    Assert.IsNotNull(handler);\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", handler.Type);\n}\n```","attachments":[],"interactionId":"afffe7a5-1822-4c85-8bd4-402d85005b7d"},"id":"ecceb10b-8358-4922-a4ed-520b51a34994","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:10:40.121Z","parentId":"4e31da22-1131-4194-9bb8-63a573d1ba3e"}
